How to run Kafka
----------------

1> download kafka > https://downloads.apache.org/kafka/3.8.0/kafka_2.12-3.8.0.tgz

Instructions
------------
1.) move the downloaded kafka file into C:/ Drive

2.) Open cmd and type cd (file path of your kafka file)

3.) paste the following code to run zookeeper.
-----------------------------------------------------------------
.\bin\windows\zookeeper-serverstart.bat .\config\zookeeper.properties
-----------------------------------------------------------------
SHOULD start the zookeeper

4.) open a new cmd

Repeat step two to work in the Kafka file

5.) paste the following code to run Kafka server.
---------------------------------------------------
.\bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat
.\config\server.properties
---------------------------------------------------
should run the kafka server

6.) open the kafka file in C:/ drive enter windows and then bin file path should look like
"C:\Kafka\bin\windows" open the cmd in this file path.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

HERE WE WILL CREATE THE TOPICS IN THE PRODUCER AND PRINT TO CONSUMER
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7.) Code to Create the topic
kafka-topics.bat --create  --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic (topic name)

8.)code for the producer
kafka-console-producer.bat --broker-list localhost:9092 --topic (topic name)
>{where you enter information for the records}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
